HEY, CAN I COME?

30
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:47,900
NO! NO!

31
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,100
OHH...PLEASE!
OHH!

32
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,300
HEY, CARL.

33
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,700
HEY, HAPPY
NEW YEAR, HANK.

34
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:01,400
YOU GOTTA START CHARGING
PEOPLE FOR THAT.

35
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:03,100
HA HA HA!

36
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,900
YEAH, IT'D PAY BETTER
THAN THE COUNTY DOES.

37
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,800
[WHISTLING
O TANNENBAUM]

38
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,600
HONEY, IT'S ME.

39
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,900
HOW YOU FEELIN'
TODAY?

40
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,500
HEY. GOOD.

41
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,100
OH, MY GOSH.

42
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,600
HE WAS SURE KICKIN'
A LOT TODAY.

43
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,000
[CAR HORN HONKING
INSISTENTLY]

44
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:47,600
UH-OH...
[HONKING]

45
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:52,200
LOOKS LIKE IT'S GONNA BE
A LONG AFTERNOON FOR YOU.

46
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,700
HE BROUGHT LOU ALONG.

47
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,000
OH, GREAT.

48
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:58,900
YEAH. I'LL JUST BE
LYIN' HERE, RELAXING.

49
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,600
OH...
HA HA HA!

50
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,900
[SPIRIT IN THE SKY
PLAYING ON RADIO]

51
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:06,600
HEY, JACOB!

52
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,100
HA HA HA!

53
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,200
WHAT'S HE
DOING HERE?

54
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,800
HE NEEDED
A RIDE HOME.

55
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,500
LITTLE OUT OF
THE WAY, ISN'T IT?

56
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,600
WE CAN DROP HIM OFF
WHEN WE'RE DONE.

57
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,200
YOU KNOW? IT'S
NO BIG DEAL, HANK.

58
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,600
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL,
HANK?

59
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,400
HEY, YOU KNOW, YOU NEED
TO SHOVEL THIS SHIT

60
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,600
OFF OF YOUR, UH...
WHATCHACALLIT DEAL THERE.

61
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,700
I'LL PAY YOU
A QUARTER TO DO IT.

62
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,800
HUH!
I COULD USE IT.

63
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:39,800
HA HA!
LOOK AT LOU.

64
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,800
HERE, HOLD THIS,
WILL YOU?

65
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,300
WANNA PUT IT
BACK THERE?

66
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,500
NO, NO,
IT'S GONNA WILT.

67
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,200
HANK,
SAY HI TO--

68
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,800
YOU DIDN'T SAY HI
TO MARY BETH.

69
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,300
OH, YEAH.
HI, MARY BETH.

70
00:05:54,300 --> 00:05:55,700
HE SAID HI,
MARY BETH.

71
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,900
HANK SAID HI.
HI, LOU.

72
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,100
COME HERE.

73
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:34,900
SOMEBODY ELSE
WAS HERE.

74
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,600
OH, I BROUGHT THOSE.

75
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,000
WHEN?

76
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,950
WELL...WHAT THE HELL
DO YOU THINK, HANK?

77
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,200
THIS IS THE ONLY DAY
WE CAN COME HERE?

78
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:47,100
WHAT THE HELL'S
WRONG WITH YOU?

79
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:50,100
HEY, JACOB!
LOOK!

80
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,800
I'M WRITING
MY NAME!

81
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,500
HANG ON A SECOND!

82
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,200
LET ME GET MRS. JOHNSON
OUT HERE!

83
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,600
I'LL HELP YOU OUT.

84
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,000
[CHUCKLING]

85
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:07,900
[PANICKED CLUCKING]

86
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:21,400
Lou: YOU KNOW WHAT
THE GUY SAYS?

87
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,500
Jacob: SAYS IT'S
THE CROCK POT--

88
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,400
OR, UH, CROCK BOX?

89
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,000
NO, NO.
PAY ATTENTION NOW--

90
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,600
OH, NO, THAT'S
THE PREACHER, SEE?

91
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:30,100
THIS IS THE COWBOY.

92
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,700
YEAH.
HE SAYS "MOO."

93
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,600
NO, NO. IT'S THE GUY
STANDING BY THE ROAD.

94
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:38,400
HE SAYS, "WHY, OFFICER,
IT'S JUST A PINE  APPLE."

95
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:40,200
HA HA HA!
HA HA!

96
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,900
YOU GET IT?
YEAH.

97
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,100
WELL, MR. ACCOUNTANT
DOESN'T GET IT.

98
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:46,200
HA HA HA HA...

99
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,000
LOOK OUT!

100
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:49,900
SHIT!

101
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,300
YOU OK, BABY?

102
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,700
GO ON, GET OUT!

103
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:55,800
[ARF ARF]

104
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:57,100
LOOK AT THAT,
MAN!

105
00:07:58,300 --> 00:07:59,400
MY TRUCK.

106
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,100
COME ON, GET OUT.

107
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,100
MARY BETH!

108
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,100
SHE'S GONNA
COME BACK.

109
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,400
HEY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?

110
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,000
IT'S A NATURE PRESERVE.
YOU KNOW THAT.

111
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:12,300
SO WHAT?

112
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,600
SO YOU CAN'T
HUNT HERE.

113
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,000
COME ON, PUT
THE GUN BACK.

114
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,700
BUT IT--BUT IT
MESSED UP MY TRUCK.

115
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,500
SO WHAT?
COME ON.

116
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,800
HEY, HEY, HANK...

117
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,400
IT'S NOT LIKE
WE'RE HUNTIN' HERE.

118
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:24,900
UH-UH. WE'RE
COLLECTIN' THE DEAD.

119
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:26,400
THAT'S RIGHT.

120
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,900
WE'RE COLLECTING
THE DEAD.

121
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,000
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

122
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,200
[LAUGHTER]

123
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,900
JUST LOOK
AT HIM...

124
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,200
HE RUNS LIKE
MY WIFE.

125
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,100
HEY, COME ON,
WAIT UP!

126
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,700
COME ON, I'M NOT DRESSED
FOR THIS SHIT!

127
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,900
[INDISTINCT TALKING
AND LAUGHTER]

128
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:08,200
MARY BETH!

129
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,350
JESUS! LOOK AT
ALL THEM BIRDS.

130
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,500
THOSE THINGS ARE ALWAYS
WAITIN' ON SOMETHING TO DIE

131
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,100
SO THEY CAN EAT IT,
RIGHT?

132
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,600
WHAT A WEIRD JOB.

133
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:36,400
WISH WE HAD
SOMETHING TO DRINK.

134
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:40,650
ALWAYS
BE PREPARED.

135
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,000
OH, THAT'S
A GOOD IDEA.

136
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:43,600
LET'S ALL START
DRINKING NOW.

137
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,200
SEE THERE?
SEE HOW HE IS?

138
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:49,400
WONK! DIT-DIT...
LIKE THAT GUY, HUH?

139
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:52,700
REMEMBER?
WONK! DIT-DIT.

140
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,800
UH-HUH.

141
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:54,700
YOU WANT SOME?

142
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:55,700
I'M NOT THIRSTY.

143
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,000
WHAT, YOU
DON'T DRINK

144
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,400
TILL AFTER 5:00?

145
00:09:58,300 --> 00:09:59,600
AFTER 5:00,
HEH HEH.

146
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,000
OR MAYBE YOU JUST
DON'T WANNA SHARE.

147
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,800
YOU'RE AFRAID YOU'LL
CATCH SOMETHING

148
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,300
FROM US, HUH?

149
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,300
[SOTTO]
YEAH.

150
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:05,800
HEY, HANK.

151
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,400
HEY! COME ON,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

152
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,400
QUIT JACKIN' AROUND.

153
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,800
NOW, YOU SEE...

154
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,200
THAT'S WHAT
YOU MIGHT CALL

155
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:15,200
AN INSINUATING
THROW. REMEMBER?

156
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,900
YOU SAID THAT TO ME
LAST TIME I SAW YOU.

157
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,400
COULDA JUST SAID
"HINT," BUT NO.

158
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,300
YOU HAD
TO PUT ON AIRS,

159
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:25,900
SHOW US ALL THEM
FANCY WORDS YOU KNOW.

160
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,800
WHAT, DO YOU SIT AROUND,
YOU THINK ABOUT THIS STUFF?

161
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,400
WHEN WAS THAT,
2 MONTHS AGO?

162
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:33,400
KISS MY ASS.

163
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,800
[CLUNK]

164
00:10:39,300 --> 00:10:40,600
WHAT THE HELL
IS IT?

165
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:49,000
Jesus Christ.

166
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,400
SHIT,
THAT'S A AIRPLANE.

167
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:53,800
Jacob:
YOU KNOW WHAT,

168
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,500
IT'S PROBABLY ONE OF
THOSE DRUNK DOCTORS.

169
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,400
THEY'RE ALWAYS CRASHING
THEIR PLANE, YOU KNOW?

170
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,400
Lou: YEAH, IT MUST'VE
COME DOWN RIGHT THERE.

171
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,500
SEE ALL THEM
BROKEN TREES, JAKE?

172
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:02,800
IT'S TOO DARK.
I CAN'T SEE.

173
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:05,900
SCRAPE SOME OF THAT SNOW
OFF THE WINDSHIELD.

174
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,500
Lou:...CAN'T SEE
A DAMN THING.

175
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,000
DOOR'S STUCK.

176
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,900
Jacob: PROBABLY
A SINGER OR SOMETHING.

177
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,500
Lou: STILL CAN'T SEE
NOTHIN' HERE.

178
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,100
STILL CAN'T SEE
ANYTHING.

179
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,600
CAN'T SEE
A DAMN THING.

180
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:33,800
I SEE THE PILOT!

181
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,500
WHAT'S HE
TALKING ABOUT?

182
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,200
SAID SOMEBODY'S
IN THERE.

183
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,000
ARE YOU OK?

184
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,400
HEY. HEY, BUDDY...

185
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,300
AAH! WHOAAA...

186
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,500
AH! AAH! AAH!

187
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,800
HEY, GET--GET OFF!

188
00:11:54,900 --> 00:11:55,600
[CROWS SQUAWKING]

189
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,200
Lou: WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON..?

190
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,100
AAH! OHH!

191
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,100
OH, GOD!

192
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,000
SHIT!

193
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,000
HEY, LEMME
OUTTA HERE.

194
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,100
GOOD GRIEF, HANK.

195
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,300
LET ME GET THIS
OFF OF HIM. HERE...

196
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,700
HANK, DID YOU--
DID YOU--

197
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:20,500
DID YOU SEE--DID YOU
SEE ALL THEM BIRDS?

198
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,300
DID I SEE THE BIRDS?

199
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,900
COME ON, HELP ME
GET OUTTA HERE.

200
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,800
HANK, PUT THAT
ON YOUR EYE.

201
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:34,800
THANKS.

202
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,850
YOU TORE YOUR COAT,
YOU KNOW.

203
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,000
OH, MY GOD...

204
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,400
OH, MY GOD!
LOOK AT THIS!

205
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,300
SHIT!

206
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,400
OH, MY GOD!

207
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,800
HOW MUCH YOU THINK
IS IN HERE?

208
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,100
GOD ALMIGHTY!
THESE ARE $100 BILLS!

209
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,000
THE WHOLE BAG'S
FULL OF 'EM!

210
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,900
IS THIS--IS IT
HA HA! REAL MONEY, LOU?

211
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,300
OH, HELL, YES,
IT'S REAL.

212
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:54,100
DON'T BE STUPID.

213
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,700
WHY WOULD SOMEBODY
BE FLYING AROUND

214
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,900
WITH THIS KIND
OF CASH?

215
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,300
YOU KNOW WHAT? I BET
IT'S DRUG MONEY.

216
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:01,300
THAT'S PROBABLY
I BET YOU'RE WHAT IT IS. RIGHT.

217
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,000
THIS GUY'S
A DOPE DEALER

218
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:02,900
BECAUSE THAT'S
WHAT THEY DO.

219
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,000
THEY FLY AROUND IN
THESE LITTLE PLANES.

220
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,600
I GUARAN-DAMN- TEE YOU.
THIS IS DIRTY MONEY.

221
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,200
THAT'S RIGHT.

222
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:07,100
I SAW IT
ON 20/20.

223
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,600
"DIRTY MONEY"?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

224
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:10,300
ARE YOU TELLING ME
IT'S COUNTERFEIT?

225
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,200
OH, NO.
NO, NO, NO.

226
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,400
NO, THIS
IS REAL.

227
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,200
WHATEVER IT IS,
IT'S A POLICE MATTER NOW.

228
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:16,500
WHAT DO YOU THINK
WE SHOULD DO?

229
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:17,400
SOMEBODY SHOULD
STAY HERE,

230
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,900
SOMEBODY SHOULD GO
AFTER THE COPS?

231
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:20,400
HOW YOU WANNA
WHAT? WORK IT?

232
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,000
LET'S THINK
THIS THROUGH.

233
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,200
WHAT?
HOLD ON!

234
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,400
WHAT IF WE DIDN'T
TURN IT IN?

235
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,600
YOU WANNA KEEP IT?

236
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,300
HA HA HA!
HE WANTS TO KEEP IT.

237
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,200
WELL,
THAT'S A HOT ONE.

238
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:36,500
WHY WOULDN'T WE?

239
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:37,800
WHY WOULDN'T WE?
YEAH.

240
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,500
BECAUSE WE'D GO
TO PRISON.  WHY?

241
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,300
WHY? BECAUSE
IT'S STEALING.

242
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,000
STEALING.
STEALING FROM WHO?

243
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,750
FROM HIM? HELL,
HE WON'T MIND.

244
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,300
HEH HEH...

245
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:49,100
OH, 'CAUSE HE'S
DEAD, RIGHT? HA HA HA!

246
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,200
HA HA! THAT'S
PRETTY FUNNY--

247
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,400
HE'S DEAD.
HE WON'T MIND.

248
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,600
I SAY WE TAKE THIS BAG
BACK TO THE TRUCK,

249
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,500
AND WE PRETEND LIKE
WE WERE NEVER HERE.

250
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,200
FUCK YEAH.
WHY NOT?

251
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,800
WHY NOT? BECAUSE
WE'D GET CAUGHT.

252
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:01,400
AW, HELL! I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT.

253
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:02,900
STAY THE HELL
OUT OF IT THEN.

254
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:04,500
YOU KNOW, WE
DON'T NEED YOU.

255
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,200
IT'D JUST BE MORE
MONEY FOR US.

256
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,300
HEY, I DON'T WANNA STUMP YOU
ANOTHER FANCY WORD, LOU,

257
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,900
BUT DOES THE TERM "ACCOMPLICE"
MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?

258
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,100
COME ON. THAT'S STUPID.

259
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,700
BUT, HANK, WHY
WOULD WE GET CAUGHT?

260
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,400
BECAUSE IT'S A LOT
OF MONEY.

261
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,100
SOMEBODY'S BOUND
TO BE LOOKING FOR IT.

262
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,000
WHEN THEY FIND
THAT PLANE

263
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:19,700
AND THE MONEY'S
NOT IN IT,

264
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,800
THEY'LL COME
BULLSHIT! LOOKING FOR US. BULLSHIT!

265
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,400
THIS IS
DIRTY MONEY!

266
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,900
AND AS FAR AS THAT
GUY'S CONCERNED,

267
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,600
THE COPS DON'T EVEN
KNOW HE EXISTS.

268
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,400
NOBODY KNOWS
ABOUT THIS...

269
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:30,300
BUT US.
SEE THERE?

270
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,300
NOBODY KNOWS
BUT US.

271
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,000
IT'S LIKE WE CAME
OUT HERE ON A HIKE,

272
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,400
AND FOUND LOST TREASURE.
RIGHT?

273
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:38,400
IT'S THE AMERICAN DREAM
IN A GODDAMN GYM BAG.

274
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,300
HE--HE JUST WANTS
TO WALK AWAY FROM IT.

275
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,000
YOU WORK FOR
THE AMERICAN DREAM.

276
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:44,000
YOU DON'T STEAL IT.

277
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,400
THEN THIS IS
EVEN BETTER.

278
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,900
IF THIS GUY'S
A DOPE DEALER,

279
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:51,000
THEN--LIKE WE'RE
TALKIN' ABOUT--

280
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,600
THEN THAT MEANS WE'RE
LIKE ROBIN HOOD.

281
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,500
OH, YEAH, AND I'LL
TELL YOU WHAT.

282
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,900
YOU GOT A BEAUTIFUL
WIFE AT HOME.

283
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,800
YOU'RE ABOUT
TO HAVE A BABY.

284
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,500
I KNOW YOU AIN'T
PULLIN' DOWN THAT MUCH

285
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:00,200
AT THE FEED MILL.

286
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:03,100
WOULDN'T YOU LOVE TO
HAVE A PIECE OF THIS?

287
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,900
HELL, YES, I WOULD,
BUT WE CAN'T JUST TAKE IT.

288
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,200
HEY, WHAT IF
THERE'S A REWARD?

289
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:08,900
MAYBE THERE'S A REWARD,
AND THEY'LL GIVE--

290
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,600
MAYBE THERE'S NOT!

291
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,500
HOW ABOUT THIS.
I TELL YOU WHAT.

292
00:15:13,300 --> 00:15:14,600
I'LL BET YOU
$10,000--

293
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,300
JUST ONE OF
THESE PACKETS--

294
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,800
THAT WHEN THEY
FIND THIS PLANE,

295
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,000
THERE'S NO MENTION
OF THIS MONEY.

296
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,000
HANK, WHY--
WHY TURN IT IN

297
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,100
UNTIL WE KNOW
WHETHER OR NOT

298
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,200
SOMEBODY'S
LOOKIN' FOR IT?

299
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:41,600
THAT'S RIGHT.

300
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,300
IF YOU SCRATCH,
THEN DON'T--DON'T ITCH.

301
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,600
IF YOU--IF IT'S--

302
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:49,200
IF IT'S BROKEN,
DON'T FIX IT. RIGHT?

303
00:15:49,300 --> 00:15:50,900
OR IF YOU--IF--IF--
IF THE--IF--IF--IF--

304
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:53,700
AND I KNOW
WHAT YOU MEAN.

305
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,500
[CAW CAW]

306
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,200
SUPPOSE I WAS
THE ONE TO KEEP IT?

307
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,100
FOR HOW LONG?

308
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,990
JUST TILL SPRING,
TILL THEY FIND THE PLANE.

309
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,000
THEN WHAT?

310
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:20,980
THEN, IF YOU'RE RIGHT AND
NOBODY MENTIONS THE MONEY,

311
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,800
WE SPLIT IT UP,
AND WE ALL LEAVE TOWN.

312
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,700
WHY SHOULD YOU
GET TO HOLD IT?

313
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,800
THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
I'LL DO IT.

314
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,700
OTHERWISE WE CAN JUST
TURN IT IN RIGHT NOW.

315
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,300
SO, WHAT, YOU MEAN--
YOU--YOU--

316
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,600
YOU DON'T TRUST US?
IS THAT WHAT YOU MEAN?

317
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,100
THAT'S A LOT OF MONEY.
I GUESS I DON'T.

318
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:40,650
LOOK, NO--NO PROMISES.
IF SOMEBODY COMES SEARCHING

319
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:41,600
FOR THE MONEY,
I'LL BURN IT.

320
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,400
I'LL BURN IT,
LISTEN, AND THAT'S IT. HANK...

321
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,200
NO. THAT'S THE ONLY WAY
I'LL DO THIS!

322
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,100
LOOK, WE GOTTA BE
AGREED ON THIS.

323
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:48,600
THAT'S THE DEAL.
THAT'S THE DEAL.

324
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,400
I HOLD ONTO IT, WE WAIT
TILL THEY FIND THE PLANE.

325
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,200
IF NOBODY MENTIONS IT,

326
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,700
WE SPLIT IT UP,
AND WE MOVE AWAY.

327
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,100
OK?

328
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:57,000
I'M IN.

329
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,400
WE COUNT IT
FIRST.

330
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,100
THAT'S PROBABLY
A GOOD IDEA.

331
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,600
I MEAN, YOU KNOW...

332
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,400
HEH HEH HEH...

333
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,300
HEH HEH...
HEH HEH...

334
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:15,300
THIS IS NUTS.

335
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:16,500
OH, MY GOD...

336
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:19,400
HEY, WHAT YOU GONNA
BUY, JAKEY BOY?

337
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,500
I'M GONNA BUY ME
A TRUCK.

338
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,400
NO. FUCK THAT.

339
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:24,700
GET SOMETHING
CLASSY.

340
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:25,300
TRANS-AM.

341
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:27,900
OH, YEAH, IN MY WILDEST
FUCKIN' DREAMS, A TRANS-AM.

342
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,800
YOU COULD BUY A FLEET
OF TRANS-AMS.

343
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,700
MARY BETH!
MARY BETH!

344
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:32,200
WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?

345
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,900
WHERE YOU
BEEN, HUH?

346
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:35,800
THERE'S SHOES
FOR BABY, HA HA!

347
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,800
Lou:...4,350,000,

348
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,900
4,360,000...
4,370,000...

349
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:54,800
4,380,000...

350
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:57,000
4,390,000...

351
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,800
$4,400,000!

352
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:03,500
ISN'T THAT GREAT?
LISTEN TO THAT.

353
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,990
LOOK AT THAT SHIT, MAN.
LOOK HOW SQUARE IT IS.

354
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,000
THAT IS COOL, HUH?

355
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,300
HOW MUCH IS THAT
APIECE?

356
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:10,800
ABOUT A MILLION
AND A...

357
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,200
A MILLION
AND WHAT? SHH!

358
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,400
A MILLION AND
A HALF? WHAT?

359
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,800
SHH! YOU
HEAR THAT?

360
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:15,700
UH-UH.

361
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,100
OH, SHIT.

362
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,800
GET IN THE TRUCK.
I'LL HANDLE THIS.

363
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:32,900
SHIT.
GO ON!

364
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:33,600
Hank: LET'S GO!

365
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:35,000
COME ON, COVER UP
THE MONEY!

366
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,400
JAKE, GET
IN THE TRUCK!

367
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:37,600
DUMMY UP.
LET'S GO!

368
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,100
COME ON!

369
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:50,900
HEY, CARL.

370
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,000
ENGINE TROUBLE,
HANK?

371
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,400
OH, I WISH.
DOG TROUBLE.

372
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,990
JACOB'S MUTT CHASED
A FOX INTO THE WOODS.

373
00:18:56,100 --> 00:18:56,500
SHE TREE IT?

374
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,800
WE THOUGHT SO, BUT JUST
WHEN WE WENT AFTER IT,

375
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,300
SHE CAME RUNNING BACK.

376
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,000
AH.

377
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,600
WHAT'D YOU DO
TO YOUR HEAD THERE?

378
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:04,700
OH. GOD, UH...

379
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:06,500
HEH. RAN INTO
A TREE BRANCH.

380
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,800
YOUR BROTHER
STILL OUT OF WORK?

381
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,200
YEAH.

382
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,300
LOU?

383
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:14,400
YEAH, HIM, TOO.

384
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:16,300
THAT'S A SHAME,
AIN'T IT?

385
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,400
WELL, WE PROBABLY BETTER
BE HEADING BACK--

386
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:21,900
HEY, HELLO, JACOB!

387
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,100
HEY, CARL,
HOW YOU DOIN'?

388
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,600
GOOD, GOOD.

389
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:26,700
I WAS BEGINNING
TO THINK

390
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,200
YOU WERE TRYING
TO AVOID ME.

391
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:29,100
I'M SORRY?

392
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,900
WELL, YOU SITTIN'
OVER THERE IN THAT TRUCK.

393
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,100
I THOUGHT YOU WAS
TRYING TO AVOID ME.

394
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,000
NO. JUST SITTIN'
IN THE TRUCK.

395
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,900
IT'S A LITTLE COLD
OUT HERE, YOU KNOW.

396
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:39,100
JUST KEEPIN' WARM.

397
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,700
WELL, WE PROBABLY
BETTER BE--

398
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,200
DID YOU TELL HIM
ABOUT THE PLANE?

399
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,600
IT SOU-SOUNDED
LIKE A PLANE.

400
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:45,600
WHAT PLANE?

401
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,700
WHAT, YOU HEARD
A PLANE?

402
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,300
UH...I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HE HEARD.

403
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,200
YOU KNOW HE'S ALWAYS
HEARING SHIT.

404
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,900
MAYBE YOU BETTER
TELL ME, JACOB.

405
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:57,300
NO, THAT'S OK.

406
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,800
WE'RE GONNA
GET ON HOME.

407
00:19:59,200 --> 00:19:59,800
ALL RIGHT.

408
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:00,500
ALL RIGHT.
COME ON, MAN.

409
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,200
IT'S NEW YEAR'S!
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.

410
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,800
Jacob:
CALL ME, CARL.

411
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:04,400
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

412
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,000
SURE YOU DON'T
NEED ANY HELP?

413
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:06,900
NO, WE'RE ALL SET.

414
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,200
THANKS.
ALL RIGHT.

415
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:08,600
GODDAMN IT!

416
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,800
I'VE SEEN YOU DO SOME
PRETTY STUPID THINGS, JACOB,

417
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:12,500
BUT THAT PRETTY MUCH
TAKES THE CAKE!

418
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,500
IT WAS MY IDEA.

419
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,800
OH, WELL, THAT'S
BRILLIANT, LOU.

420
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,400
NOW WHEN THEY FIND
THE PLANE,

421
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:18,900
AND THEY REALIZE
THE MONEY'S GONE,

422
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:20,700
THEY'LL KNOW RIGHT OFF
WHO TOOK IT.

423
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,100
WELL, THAT'S--

424
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:23,600
THAT'S WHAT'S COOL
ABOUT IT, THOUGH.

425
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,300
I MEAN, WE WOULDN'T
TELL SOMEBODY

426
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,900
IF WE WERE THE ONES
THAT DID IT.

427
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,000
IT'S NOT LIKE HE SAID

428
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,700
THAT YOU ACTUALLY SAW
A PLANE GOING DOWN.

429
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,500
JUST YOU THOUGHT YOU
MIGHT'VE HEARD ONE

430
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:32,500
WITH ENGINE TROUBLE.

431
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,000
YOU WANT ME TO
BURN THE MONEY?!

432
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,800
I AM NOT GOING
TO PRISON OVER THIS!

433
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,700
IF IT LOOKS LIKE THERE'S
EVEN THE SLIGHTEST CHANCE

434
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,300
OF US GETTING CAUGHT,

435
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,000
I SWEAR TO GOD,
IT'S ALL GONNA VANISH!

436
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,200
YOU UNDERSTAND?

437
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,000
"IT WAS A PINE APPLE."

438
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,100
HEE HEE HEE HEE HEE...

439
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:09,300
[GROANING] OH, GOD...
THIS IS GONNA BE FUN.

440
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,400
Woman: WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN?!

441
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:15,900
YOU COME WHEN
I'M ALWAYS FINISHED.

442
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,400
I'M FINISHED,
YOU ASSHOLE!

443
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,700
HEY, NANCY!

444
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:23,600
DON'T--
DON'T HIT--

445
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:24,900
DON'T HIT
MARY BETH.

446
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,500
[LOW] REMEMBER,
NOBODY KNOWS ABOUT THIS.

447
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:27,400
THAT INCLUDES NANCY.

448
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,200
SHE'LL HAVE TO FIND OUT
ABOUT IT SOONER OR LATER.

449
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,500
SHE'LL WONDER WHERE ALL
THE MONEY'S COMING FROM.

450
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,600
2 HOURS LATE!

451
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:34,000
OW! STOP IT!

452
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,800
TELL HER WHEN WE DECIDE
IT'S SAFE TO KEEP IT,

453
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:37,700
BUT NOT BEFORE THEN.

454
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,100
THEN THE SAME GOES
FOR SARAH.

455
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:41,200
OF COURSE.

456
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,200
[THUNK]

457
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,000
DAMN IT!

458
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:43,700
Nancy: COME ON!

459
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:45,200
YOU PROMISED TO
SHOVEL THE WALK,

460
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:47,100
YOU LAZY SON
OF A BITCH!

461
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:47,900
CALM DOWN, BABY.

462
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,800
I GOT A GOOD REASON
FOR BEING LATE. WHAT?

463
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:51,900
SEE YOU, LOU!

464
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,800
[INDISTINCT ARGUING]

465
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,100
YOU KNOW, I BET
HE'S TELLING HER.

466
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:59,000
THAT GUY CAN'T
KEEP A SECRET.

467
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:13,400
HEY, HONEY.

468
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,400
HEY.

469
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,000
WHERE YOU BEEN?

470
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,100
I WAS STARTING TO GET
WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

471
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,200
SORRY I'M LATE.

472
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,400
OH, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

473
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,400
HEY.

474
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:28,900
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR HEAD?

475
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:30,300
IT'S OK. IT'S
JUST A SCRATCH.

476
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,800
IT'S ALL BLOODY.

477
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,000
CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

478
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:35,400
YEAH, SURE.

479
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,400
WHAT IF YOU WERE
WALKING IN THE WOODS--

480
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,000
IT'S NOT DEEP.

481
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:41,600
AND YOU FOUND
A BAG FULL OF MONEY,

482
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,300
LET'S SAY $4 MILLION...

483
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:46,800
WOULD YOU KEEP IT?

484
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,500
