00:35:59,500 --> 00:36:01,100
TV:  HE WAS APPARENTLY
TRYING TO CROSS

729
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,500
ALONG THIS BANK OF SNOW

730
00:36:02,700 --> 00:36:04,990
WHEN HIS SNOWMOBILE
SLIPPED OVER THE EDGE

731
00:36:05,100 --> 00:36:07,990
THROWING HIM INTO THE ICY
WATERS OF ANDERS CREEK.

732
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,100
WRIGHT COUNTY DEPUTIES
RECOVERED THE BODY

733
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:13,600
SHORTLY BEFORE
4:00 THIS AFTERNOON.

734
00:36:13,900 --> 00:36:16,300
A TRAGIC BEGINNING
TO THIS NEW YEAR

735
00:36:16,500 --> 00:36:17,800
FOR ONE LOCAL FAMILY.

736
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,200
BACK TO YOU, PAUL.

737
00:36:20,100 --> 00:36:21,200
THANKS, TRACY.

738
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,300
I WISH YOU HADN'T
TOLD JACOB.

739
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,200
I WISH HE STILL THOUGHT
THAT HE DID IT.

740
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:35,200
DOES IT SCARE YOU?

741
00:36:35,700 --> 00:36:36,600
YEAH, IT SCARES ME.

742
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:37,600
WHAT IF HE TELLS SOMEBODY?

743
00:36:37,700 --> 00:36:38,900
I MEAN, WHAT I DID.

744
00:36:38,900 --> 00:36:40,800
WHAT YOU DID?

745
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:43,000
WELL, I KNOW THAT
YOU ONLY DID IT

746
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:44,200
BECAUSE YOU FELT TRAPPED.

747
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,500
THAT YOU COULDN'T
FIND ANY OTHER WAY.

748
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:47,600
WOULD YOU HAVE DONE
THE SAME THING?

749
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:50,400
I MEAN, IF YOU'D BEEN
THERE INSTEAD OF ME?

750
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,990
I--I--I JUST NEED TO
KNOW IF IT'S POSSIBLE.

751
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,730
OH, HONEY.

752
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:18,200
YOU LISTENING TO ME,
HANK?

753
00:37:18,700 --> 00:37:21,600
EVERY MONDAY I COME DOWN
HERE, BUY 2 BAGS OF FEED

754
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:23,200
REGULAR AS CLOCK WORK.

755
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:25,500
2 BAGS OF WHEAT
4 TIMES A MONTH.

756
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:28,200
THAT'S 8 BAGS I'M SUPPOSED
TO BE BILLED FOR.

757
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:29,900
I DON'T KNOW HOW ELSE
TO GET THROUGH TO YOU.

758
00:37:29,900 --> 00:37:31,600
DECEMBER STARTED
ON A MONDAY, MR. SCHMITT.

759
00:37:31,700 --> 00:37:33,300
SO THERE WERE 5 MONDAYS
IN THE MONTH.

760
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:33,900
SO YOU CAME IN HERE 5--

761
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:35,800
ARE YOU TELLING ME THERE
WERE 5 WEEKS LAST MONTH?

762
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:38,600
NO, SIR, I'M TELLING YOU
THERE WERE 5 MONDAYS.

763
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:39,600
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

764
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:40,900
EXCUSE ME.
I GOT IT.

765
00:37:41,700 --> 00:37:42,300
YEAH.

766
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:43,900
Jacob: HEY, HANK,
IT'S ME.

767
00:37:43,900 --> 00:37:44,800
HANG ON A SECOND.

768
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,600
LISTEN, CHECK THAT
CALENDAR OVER THERE

769
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:48,600
IF YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,
SIR.

770
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:49,500
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

771
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,100
WELL, I'M A LITTLE BUSY
RIGHT NOW, JACOB.

772
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:51,900
WHAT IS IT?

773
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:53,500
OK, LISTEN, CAN YOU
MEET ME AT THE FARM?

774
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:55,700
WHAT FARM?
OUR FARM.

775
00:37:56,300 --> 00:37:57,600
LOOK, UH,
WHAT IS IT?

776
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:00,400
ON YOUR LUNCH BREAK.
12:30, OK?

777
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:03,600
HEY, ARE WE STRAIGHT
ON THIS, MR. SCHMITT?

778
00:38:04,300 --> 00:38:05,600
THANKS FOR COMING IN.

779
00:38:07,100 --> 00:38:08,700
LOOK, I CAN'T DRIVE
OUT THERE RIGHT--

780
00:38:09,500 --> 00:38:10,500
JACOB?

781
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:33,800
JACOB?

782
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:37,100
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

783
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:40,300
LOOK OUT!
HA HA HA HA HA.

784
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:41,800
WHAT THE HELL'D YOU
DRAG ME OUT HERE FOR?

785
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:43,200
LISTEN TO THIS.
I'M GONNA BUY IT BACK.

786
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:44,700
I'M GONNA FIX IT UP.
I'M GONNA REBUILD IT

787
00:38:44,700 --> 00:38:45,800
JUST LIKE IT WAS
BEFORE MOM AND DAD DIED.

788
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:48,900
WHOA, WHOA. COME ON, WAIT, WAIT.
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH ALL THIS.

789
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:50,200
WE'VE BEEN OVER THIS.

790
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:52,800
ONCE WE SPLIT UP THE MONEY,
WE'VE GOTTA LEAVE.

791
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,200
WE HAVE TO GO.

792
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:57,400
WHAT DO YOU--WHAT DO
YOU WANT ME TO DO,

793
00:38:57,500 --> 00:38:59,990
JUST LIKE THAT, JUST
DRIVE OFF BY MYSELF?

794
00:39:02,400 --> 00:39:03,200
WELL, I MEAN,
SUPPOSE YOU STAY.

795
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:05,000
WHERE ARE YOU GONNA TELL
PEOPLE YOU GOT THE MONEY?

796
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:06,800
OH, THAT'S EASY.

797
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,400
WE JUST TELL PEOPLE
THAT SARAH

798
00:39:08,800 --> 00:39:10,300
INHERITED SOME MONEY.
IT'S EASY.

799
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:12,900
NOBODY AROUND HERE KNOWS
ANYTHING ABOUT HER FAMILY.

800
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:16,600
YOU GUYS COULDA JUST
BOUGHT THE FARM, YOU KNOW,

801
00:39:16,700 --> 00:39:19,100
AND THEN LEFT ME TO RUN IT.

802
00:39:19,700 --> 00:39:20,300
IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

803
00:39:20,300 --> 00:39:22,000
I THOUGHT THIS WAS
GONNA MAKE YOU HAPPY.

804
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:23,300
JACOB...

805
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:26,800
FARMING? COME ON.

806
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:30,800
YOU DON'T JUST BUY A FARM.
YOU GOTTA--YOU GOTTA WORK IT.

807
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:34,200
YOU GOTTA KNOW
ABOUT MACHINERY AND SEED.

808
00:39:35,100 --> 00:39:36,200
I KNOW THAT.

809
00:39:36,500 --> 00:39:37,600
NO, YOU DON'T.

810
00:39:37,600 --> 00:39:38,700
FERTILIZERS, PESTICIDES,
HERBICIDES,

811
00:39:38,700 --> 00:39:40,300
DRAINAGE, IRRIGATION,
THE WEATHER?

812
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,200
COME ON, YOU DON'T KNOW
ABOUT ANY OF THAT STUFF.

813
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,500
YOU'RE GONNA END UP
JUST LIKE DAD.

814
00:39:44,500 --> 00:39:46,900
WHY DO YOU THINK HE
ENDED UP LIKE THAT?

815
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:48,700
I'LL TELL YOU HOW HE
ENDED UP LIKE THAT.

816
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:50,900
HE HAD 2 MORTGAGES RIDING
ON THE PLACE.

817
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:52,800
HE COULDN'T MAKE THE PAYMENTS.

818
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,400
WHERE DO YOU THINK
THE MONEY WENT?

819
00:39:54,300 --> 00:39:55,400
HE WAS A BAD BUSINESSMAN.

820
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:56,600
WHERE DO YOU THINK
THE MONEY WENT?

821
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:58,300
NO, YOU THINK HE SPENT
IT ALL ON THE FARM?

822
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,950
I'LL TELL YOU EXACTLY
WHERE THE MONEY WENT.

823
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:02,300
4 YEARS OF COLLEGE, BUD.

824
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:05,300
YEAH, DIDN'T YOU EVER THINK
ABOUT HOW HE PAID FOR THAT?

825
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:07,500
DIDN'T THAT EVER
OCCUR TO YOU?

826
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:08,600
NO, MY TUITION WAS--

827
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:10,200
LISTEN, I'M SUPPOSED
TO GET THE FARM!

828
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,100
WHAT DO I GET?!

829
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,600
I'M SUPPOSED
TO GET THE FARM.

830
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:20,600
YOU GOT--YOU GOT
THE WHOLE WORLD. YOU CAN...

831
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:22,900
I DON'T WANNA HEAR THAT.

832
00:40:28,700 --> 00:40:30,600
YOU CAN GO ANYWHERE
YOU WANT.

833
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:36,900
THIS IS WHAT I WANT.

834
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:40,800
THIS IS--THIS IS WHERE
I WANNA BE.

835
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:43,400
IT'S MY HOME, HANK.

836
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,000
SHIT.

837
00:41:21,900 --> 00:41:23,000
HEY, HONEY.

838
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:23,500
WHAT?

839
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:25,000
I WANNA SHOW YOU
SOMETHING.

840
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:28,500
WHAT IS IT?

841
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:29,000
I GOT THIS.

842
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:30,700
I HAD IT SENT OVER
FROM THE OTHER BRANCH.

843
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,600
LOOK. HERE IT IS.

844
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:34,900
"HEIRESS'S BODY
ID'D BY FEDS."

845
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,500
$4.4 MILLION RANSOM.

846
00:41:37,700 --> 00:41:39,900
YOU SEE? THIS PERSON
NOBODY KNOWS

847
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:42,200
HAS JUST DISAPPEARED
RIGHT INTO THIN AIR.

848
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:45,300
DO YOU RECOGNIZE ONE
OF THEM FROM THE PLANE?

849
00:41:45,700 --> 00:41:46,800
I CAN'T TELL.

850
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:48,900
HIS FACE WAS...

851
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:53,700
WHAT?

852
00:41:53,700 --> 00:41:54,600
THIS CHANGES IT.

853
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:55,700
WHY IS THAT?

854
00:41:57,500 --> 00:42:00,200
WE CAN'T SAY IT ISN'T
STEALING ANYMORE.

855
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:03,000
WELL, HANK, IT'S
ALWAYS BEEN STEALING.

856
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,400
WE JUST DIDN'T KNOW WHO
WE WERE STEALING FROM.

857
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:06,300
WE THOUGHT IT WAS DRUG MONEY.

858
00:42:06,400 --> 00:42:08,100
WE THOUGHT IT WAS MONEY
THAT WE COULD FIND--

859
00:42:08,200 --> 00:42:09,100
NO, YOU THOUGHT THAT.

860
00:42:09,100 --> 00:42:10,500
THIS IS GOOD.
I'M GLAD--

861
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:11,600
IT'S GOOD?

862
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:12,600
YES, IT'S GOOD WE KNOW
WHERE IT'S FROM,

863
00:42:12,700 --> 00:42:13,900
BECAUSE I WAS STARTING
TO GET WORRIED.

864
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:15,300
I THOUGHT THAT IT MIGHT
BE COUNTERFEIT OR MARKED.

865
00:42:15,300 --> 00:42:16,700
IT MIGHT STILL BE MARKED.

866
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:18,700
NO, IT SAYS RIGHT HERE.

867
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,200
LOOK. DENOMINATION
IN UNMARKED BILLS.

868
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,500
UNMARKED.

869
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:24,000
YOU SEE?

870
00:42:23,900 --> 00:42:26,400
YOU'RE JUST BEING
PARANOID, HANK.

871
00:42:26,500 --> 00:42:28,700
IT'S OVER. IT'S GOOD.

872
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,200
Man: SARAH?

873
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:32,900
WOULD YOU
COME HERE, PLEASE?

874
00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:34,800
SURE. OK. JUST A SECOND.

875
00:42:35,300 --> 00:42:36,900
I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT.

876
00:43:03,100 --> 00:43:04,100
[BANGING]

877
00:43:31,700 --> 00:43:32,900
HA HA HA HA HA.

878
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:33,900
JESUS.

879
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,900
HEY, COME ON, HANK.
OPEN UP.

880
00:43:36,900 --> 00:43:39,400
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

881
00:43:39,700 --> 00:43:40,400
HEY, MR. ACCOUNTANT.

882
00:43:40,500 --> 00:43:42,100
WELL, I'VE COME TO MAKE
A TINY WITHDRAWAL.

883
00:43:42,100 --> 00:43:43,900
GO HOME. TURN AROUND
AND GO HOME RIGHT NOW.

884
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,800
OH, COME ON, IT'S
FREEZING OUT HERE, HANK.

885
00:43:45,900 --> 00:43:46,900
SHH! KEEP IT DOWN.

886
00:43:46,900 --> 00:43:48,000
INVITE ME IN.

887
00:43:48,100 --> 00:43:49,500
ALL RIGHT,
JUST FOR A SECOND.

888
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:53,400
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS SHIT.

889
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:55,100
I GOTTA GET UP
AND GO TO WORK.

890
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:57,400
I WANT MY SHARE.

891
00:43:57,700 --> 00:43:58,400
WHAT?

892
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,600
I DO. I WANT MY SHARE.

893
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:02,100
I DON'T HAVE THE MONEY HERE,

894
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,100
AND EVEN IF I DID,
I WOULDN'T GIVE YOU ANY.

895
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:06,600
OH, COME ON, NOW.

896
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:07,900
LOOK, JUST BECAUSE
YOU HAVE IT

897
00:44:07,900 --> 00:44:11,200
DOESN'T MEAN IT'S YOURS.
PART OF THAT IS MY MONEY.

898
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:14,100
PART OF IT MIGHT BE
YOUR MONEY...

899
00:44:14,300 --> 00:44:15,600
IF WE DECIDE TO KEEP IT.

900
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,500
THE PLAN WAS TO SIT
ON THE MONEY

901
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,400
TILL WE DECIDE THAT
IT'S SAFE TO KEEP IT.

902
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:21,300
WHY ARE YOU COMING OVER HERE
WITH THIS SHIT?

903
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:22,800
ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

904
00:44:22,900 --> 00:44:24,200
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

905
00:44:24,100 --> 00:44:25,700
JUST GIVE ME
ONE PACKET, OK?

906
00:44:25,800 --> 00:44:26,800
JUST ONE PACKET.

907
00:44:26,900 --> 00:44:31,200
AND I'LL COME BACK
LATER FOR THE REST.

908
00:44:31,700 --> 00:44:35,600
ASK ME AGAIN, AND I'LL GO
BURN IT TOMORROW MORNING.

909
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,600
IS THAT CLEAR?

910
00:44:40,500 --> 00:44:41,500
BLUFF.

911
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:42,100
WHAT?

912
00:44:42,100 --> 00:44:44,600
IT'S A BLUFF.
B-L-U-F-F.

913
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:47,600
OH, THEN WHY DON'T YOU
CALL IT THEN

914
00:44:47,900 --> 00:44:49,300
AND JUST SEE WHAT HAPPENS?

915
00:44:50,100 --> 00:44:50,800
YEAH.

916
00:44:50,900 --> 00:44:52,100
ALL RIGHT. OK.

917
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:53,100
SEE, JACOB TOLD ME

918
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:55,800
A LITTLE SECRET,
MISTER ACCOUNTANT.

919
00:44:55,900 --> 00:44:59,800
I KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
TO DWIGHT STEPHANSON.

920
00:45:04,100 --> 00:45:05,600
YOU DRANK TOO MUCH.

921
00:45:06,100 --> 00:45:08,100
I WANT ONE
OF THOSE PACKETS.

922
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:12,200
WELL, I TOLD YOU,
I DON'T HAVE THE MONEY HERE,

923
00:45:12,500 --> 00:45:14,400
AND I HID IT AWAY
FROM THE HOUSE.

924
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:15,500
MM-HMM. WELL,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

925
00:45:15,700 --> 00:45:16,900
IT'D BE A SHAME
IF SOMEBODY

926
00:45:16,900 --> 00:45:19,600
WAS TO DROP A NOTE
TO CARL JENKINS

927
00:45:19,900 --> 00:45:20,900
SAYING THERE
MIGHT JUST BE

928
00:45:20,900 --> 00:45:22,400
A LITTLE SOMETHING
SUSPICIOUS ABOUT

929
00:45:22,400 --> 00:45:24,300
DWIGHT STEPHANSON'S
ACCIDENT.

930
00:45:24,800 --> 00:45:26,300
HE JUST DROVE OFF
THAT BRIDGE?

931
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:28,600
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?
DO YOU?!

932
00:45:28,800 --> 00:45:30,100
COME ON. JESUS, LOU.

933
00:45:30,500 --> 00:45:32,600
REMEMBER, YOU'RE A THIEF, TOO.

934
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:34,200
WE'RE ALL IN THIS TOGETHER.

935
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:37,700
IF ONE OF US GOES TO JAIL,
WE ALL DO.

936
00:45:50,500 --> 00:45:51,500
OH, GOD.

937
00:45:54,300 --> 00:45:56,600
I NEED MY SHARE, HANK.

938
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:58,200
I DO.

939
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:01,200
I'M BROKE...

940
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:04,200
AND I OWE PEOPLE MONEY.

941
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:06,000
CHRIST, LOU,
I MEAN WH-WH...

942
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:10,600
I NEED SOME
HELP HERE, MAN.

943
00:46:12,900 --> 00:46:15,100
OK, JUST WAIT HERE.

944
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:32,300
HERE, HERE.

945
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:35,100
$40?

946
00:46:35,500 --> 00:46:36,200
THAT'S ALL I GOT.

947
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:37,400
MAYBE I CAN GO TO THE BANK

948
00:46:37,500 --> 00:46:40,400
AND GET YOU A LOAN OUT
OF OUR SAVINGS.

949
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:41,900
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK.

950
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,700
THE MONEY'S A DAY'S DRIVE
FROM HERE.

951
00:46:43,700 --> 00:46:45,400
EVEN IF I WANTED GO GET IT,
I CAN'T GO GET IT,

952
00:46:45,700 --> 00:46:47,600
NOT TILL SARAH
HAS THE BABY.

953
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:49,000
A DAY'S DRIVE?!

954
00:46:48,900 --> 00:46:49,600
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

955
00:46:49,700 --> 00:46:52,900
I PUT IT IN A STORAGE LOCKER
ABOVE THE INTERSTATE.

956
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:54,600
WHAT THE HELL IS IT
DOING IN A STORAGE--

957
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:57,300
SHH! IT'S SAFE.
DON'T WORRY, ALL RIGHT?

958
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:58,900
I DIDN'T WANT IT NEAR US

959
00:46:58,900 --> 00:47:00,500
IN CASE WE COME UNDER
ANY SUSPICION.

960
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:02,000
HOW THE HELL'S
THAT GONNA HAPPEN?

961
00:47:02,100 --> 00:47:02,700
HOW'S THAT GONNA HAPPEN?

962
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:04,800
HOW ABOUT CARL KNOWING
ABOUT THE PLANE, HUH?

963
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:07,200
WHO'S IDEA WAS THAT?

